'''''Lost Princess Road''''' was a ballad penned by an unknown author about the mysterious disappearance of Princess [[Darseera]] from the gardens of her fortified home in the [[Purple Hills]] sometime in the third century before [[Dalereckoning]] began.<ref group="note">A likely candidate is the [[-261 DR|Year of the Lost Princess, −261 DR]], but the source does not state this explicitly. The stanza that prevented her name from being lost in the mists of time was:{{Cite dragon/268/The New Adventures of Volo: Lost Princess Road|88}}

{{Quote|Where stars and moon steal away<br />
There is fair Darseera gone<br />
Where that is, none can say<br />
Mourn her going, everyone.|An excerpt from ''Lost Princess Road''}}
